          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for study and consultation and inquires into theories of knowledge about the self (ātman), its place in the cycle of life and death (saṃsāra), and its place in relationship to the Hindu deity Śiva, envisioned as the highest Lord of the universe. Contains discussion of mantras and sound. Text is often named as one of the so-called Yoga upaniṣads, which were likely composed in the fourteenth century or later.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Amṛtabiṇḍūpaniṣad</title>
              <title type="vernacular">अमृतबिण्डूपनिषद्</title>
